summary: The document is a memorandum from Harold F. Swenson, Chief of WH/SA/CI, dated 20 May 1964. It details the rejection of an apartment at Hunting Towers, Apt #731 West, Mount Vernon Avenue, Alexandria, Virginia, for AMMUG-1's use due to its exposure to KUBARK staffers and agent assets. The memorandum mentions several individuals connected to various operations, necessitating the search for another apartment for AMMUG-1.
key_findings: The apartment at Hunting Towers was rejected for AMMUG-1's use due to exposure concerns.
Exposure to KUBARK staffers and agent assets was the primary reason for the rejection.
Key individuals mentioned include Mr. Delf Luim (AMDIXIE-1), Mr. Mike Kline (AMTOUT), Horace Speed (AMCASH), Lou De Santi (AMNIP-1), and Dr. Winston.
The necessity of securing another apartment for AMMUG-1 was highlighted.
